
######################################
The BlobSeer back end for Cumulus - setup guide
######################################

The Cumulus interface for the Blobseer system can be enabled by the following files to the pycb directory in the Cumulus source code.
		pycb/cbBlobseerBackend.py
		pycb/__init__.py



Dependencies:

The BlobSeer back-end has one dependency:

 1. The fblobseer.so library, which contains the boost.python C++ module that exposes a python interface to the BlobSeer client operations.
The fblobseer library can be obtained by compiling the BlobSeer Namespace Manager:
	svn checkout svn://scm.gforge.inria.fr/svn/blobseer/contrib/NamespaceManager
 
 

######################################
How to run the BlobSeer back end
######################################

Two configuration files are supplied in the config directory.
- .s3cfg -> the s3cmd configuration file; it can be used to change the size of the transfer block.
- cumulus.ini -> the Cumulus configuration file

The BlobSeer back-end can be easily plugged in by performing a set of changes in the Cumulus configuration file (cumulus.ini):

[backend]
type=blobseer
config_file=/home/acarpena/bsScripts/conf/running.cfg
block_size=1048576

where:
- config_file -> the BlobSeer configuration file. More details about using it in the BlobSeer tutorial:
	http://blobseer.gforge.inria.fr/doku.php?id=tutorial:deployment
		and in the Namespace Manager's README.
- block_size  -> the page size used in blobSeer

To run the Cumulus server, first export the path to the fblobseer.so library:
export PYTHONPATH=$NAMESPACE_MANAGER_HOME/FBlobseerClient/bindings/python
(this is the default path where the library is built)

Run Cumulus:
$CUMULUS_HOME/bin/cumulus




